38
00:02:17,934 --> 00:02:20,267
喂?
Huh?

39
00:02:23,100 --> 00:02:25,267
不错
Hmm.

40
00:02:27,534 --> 00:02:30,334
啊哈
Ahh.

41
00:02:30,334 --> 00:02:31,601
- 这边 放我出去  - 不
- Over here, let me out.  - No.

42
00:02:31,601 --> 00:02:34,634
- 把钥匙给我!  - 不 不行 你太暴力  
- Give me the keys!  - No, no, too violent.

43
00:02:34,634 --> 00:02:37,733
- 放了我!  - 你太懒 你太笨
- Take me!  - Sloppy, too stupid.

44
00:02:37,733 --> 00:02:40,934
你呢... 太狂
Too... ambitious.

45
00:02:40,934 --> 00:02:43,267
至于你 
You.

46
00:02:43,267 --> 00:02:45,234
我很喜欢你的"职业"
I love your work.

47
00:02:45,234 --> 00:02:47,267
前途无量
Big future.

48
00:02:47,267 --> 00:02:48,634
嘿 出去后要小心 
Hey, be careful.

49
00:02:48,634 --> 00:02:51,000
余震会不断来袭的
There's liable to be aftershocks.

50
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,568
哦 我还挺期待的呢
Oh, I'm counting on it.

51
00:03:12,834 --> 00:03:16,867

绿箭侠 第二季 第七集

52
00:03:28,134 --> 00:03:30,367
Queen先生 你母亲的案子怎么样了?
Mr. Queen, what are your mother's chances?

53
00:03:30,367 --> 00:03:33,601
她是在接受防自杀观察吗?
Is she on suicide watch?

54
00:03:33,601 --> 00:03:35,668
Queen先生 有什么想说的吗?
Mr. Queen, can you give us any comment?

55
00:03:35,668 --> 00:03:38,000
这不公平 他们又不是要受审的人
It's not fair. They're not the ones on trial.

56
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:41,134
Jean Loring会一直用他们来博取大众同情的
That won't stop Jean Loring from using them as props to drum up sympathy.

57
00:03:41,134 --> 00:03:43,000
你似乎对此不太关心
You don't seem overly concerned.

58
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:45,934
她在电视直播中承认自己是共犯
She confessed to being an accomplice on live television.

59
00:03:45,934 --> 00:03:48,334
她还说是Malcolm Merlyn强迫她的
She also sad that Malcolm Merlyn coerced her.

60
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:52,301
你掌握了什么?
You have something, don't you?

61
00:03:52,301 --> 00:03:54,767
Adam 我认为作为合伙律师
I thought I was your co-counsel, Adam.

62
00:03:54,767 --> 00:03:57,367
如果你掌握了本案的关键证据 难道不应该告诉我吗?
If you're holding a trump card, don't you think maybe you should share it with me?

63
00:03:57,367 --> 00:03:59,434
这将是一场别开生面的审判
It's going to be a good trial.

64
00:03:59,434 --> 00:04:02,700
进去吧
Come on, let's get inside.

65
00:04:11,201 --> 00:04:12,900
你们没必要赶尽杀绝
You don't have to do this.

66
00:04:12,900 --> 00:04:14,668
Ivo给我们下的命令
Ivo says we do.

67
00:04:14,668 --> 00:04:16,100
你的朋友对他们是个威胁
Your friends are a danger to his men.

68
00:04:16,100 --> 00:04:17,733
闭嘴 快点走
Go. Quick and quiet.

69
00:04:17,733 --> 00:04:19,568
Slade! Shado! 快跑!
Slade! Shado! Run!

70
00:04:32,733 --> 00:04:34,367
里面没人
There's no one here.

71
00:04:36,700 --> 00:04:39,334
他们一定逃跑了
They must have moved on from their position.

72
00:04:39,334 --> 00:04:41,134
炸弹已安好 这是引爆器
Chargers are set. Here's the detonator.

73
00:04:41,134 --> 00:04:43,800
让他们在这里无处藏身
Make sure they have no place to return to.

74
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:45,767
去吧
Go.

75
00:04:45,767 --> 00:04:48,668
至于你
And you.

76
00:04:48,668 --> 00:04:50,434
给我们带路去墓地
Now you're going to take us to the graves.

77
00:04:50,434 --> 00:04:52,767
走吧 把他弄起来
Let's go. Get him up.

78
00:04:54,267 --> 00:04:57,267
注意四周
Let's get clear.

79
00:04:59,434 --> 00:05:02,367
找到引爆装置了吗?
Did you find the detonator?

80
00:05:02,367 --> 00:05:04,467
找到了
Yes.

81
00:05:06,367 --> 00:05:08,067
我们很幸运
We were lucky.

82
00:05:08,067 --> 00:05:11,534
我很幸运 你是幸运女神
I was lucky. You were good.

83
00:05:11,534 --> 00:05:13,434
随便怎么说吧...
Either way...

84
00:05:13,434 --> 00:05:15,134
他们抓住了Oliver
They have Oliver.

85
00:05:15,134 --> 00:05:17,568
我要去救他
I'm going after him.

86
00:05:17,568 --> 00:05:19,668
我跟你一起
Not alone.

87
00:05:19,668 --> 00:05:22,568
你走路都费劲
You can barely walk.

88
00:05:22,568 --> 00:05:24,800
这里不能久留
All the more reason not to stay here.

89
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:28,134
不能让他们再来把我炸飞
Give them another chance at blowing me up.

90
00:05:33,934 --> 00:05:35,434
你们还好吧?
Are you two ok?

91
00:05:35,434 --> 00:05:37,267
这个问题应该我来问你
I should be asking you that question.

92
00:05:37,267 --> 00:05:38,367
我没事
I'll be fine.

93
00:05:38,367 --> 00:05:40,401
你好像得了流感
You look like you have the flu.

94
00:05:40,401 --> 00:05:42,434
要是得了流感 那当初的疫苗就白接种了
If that's true, I shouldn't have wasted my time getting vaccinated.

95
00:05:42,434 --> 00:05:44,800
Diggle 不管怎样 你还是回去休息一下吧
Diggle, whatever it is, just go home.

96
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:47,067
Oliver 我没事
Oliver, listen, I can take care of things.

97
00:05:47,067 --> 00:05:49,100
我们不会有事的 
No, we'll be fine, all right?

98
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:51,067
回去休息吧 别逼我叫警察把你拖回去
Go rest. And don't make me call a cop.

99
00:05:51,067 --> 00:05:54,534
有几个警察在附近哟
There are a few of them around here.

100
00:06:19,733 --> 00:06:22,534
我被迫参与
I have been complicit in an undertaking

101
00:06:22,534 --> 00:06:25,334
一项恐怖的阴谋...
with one horrible purpose...

102
00:06:25,334 --> 00:06:29,634
摧毁贫民区的一切
to destroy the Glades and everyone in it.

103
00:06:29,634 --> 00:06:32,100
阴谋得逞了 贫民区被摧毁了
And it worked. The Glades were destroyed.

104
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:34,334
人们流离失所
Homes and lives were lost.

105
00:06:34,334 --> 00:06:36,467
全都归罪于她
All because of her actions.

106
00:06:36,467 --> 00:06:38,934
虽然她悔过了 
True, she had second thoughts, remorse which

107
00:06:38,934 --> 00:06:41,867
因自责而发表了以上声明
compelled her to deliver this statement.

108
00:06:41,867 --> 00:06:44,034
但作为那天
But on behalf of the 503 lives

109
00:06:44,034 --> 00:06:46,367
丧生的503人的代表
that were extinguished that day,

110
00:06:46,367 --> 00:06:50,000
我觉得Moira Queen的自责声明来的太迟了
I say, Moira Queen, your remorse comes too late.

111
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:52,201
在过去的五年里
For the last five years,

112
00:06:52,201 --> 00:06:54,334
他以我和我家人的生命
under the threat for my life

113
00:06:54,334 --> 00:06:56,034
来威胁我...
and the lives of my family...

114
00:06:56,034 --> 00:06:59,034
为什么这些威胁会让她妥协?
Why wouldn't those threats silence her?

115
00:06:59,034 --> 00:07:02,334
为什么Moira Queen非常害怕?
Why wouldn't Moira Queen be terrified?

116
00:07:02,334 --> 00:07:05,034
因为Malcolm Merlyn谋杀了她的第一任丈夫
Malcolm Merlyn killed her first husband,

117
00:07:05,034 --> 00:07:08,367
然后绑架了她的第二人丈夫 她怎么能不担忧自己的生命呢?
abducted her second. Why wouldn't she be in fear for her life?

118
00:07:08,367 --> 00:07:11,000
怎么能不担心她孩子的安危呢?
For the lives of her children?

119
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:13,534
你碰到这种情况会怎么做?
What would you do?

120
00:07:13,534 --> 00:07:15,568
要是你孩子的生命
If it were your children in the crosshairs

121
00:07:15,568 --> 00:07:17,900
被一个疯子威胁 你会怎么做?
of a mad man's rage?

122
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:23,634
他们说S.T.A.R.实验室的粒子加速器
They say S.T.A.R. Lab's particle accelerator

123
00:07:23,634 --> 00:07:25,967
将会按计划开启
will be turned on right on schedule.

124
00:07:25,967 --> 00:07:27,833
来自其他方面的报道
In other news, we have just received word

125
00:07:27,833 --> 00:07:30,401
有消息称控辩双方就Moira Queen的案子
that both sides have now completed their opening statements

126
00:07:30,401 --> 00:07:32,568
都做了陈述
in the Moira Queen trial.

127
00:07:32,568 --> 00:07:34,501
别误会 我觉得你看起来很不好
Don't take this the wrong way, but you look disgusting.

128
00:07:34,501 --> 00:07:36,501
没错 Felicity 我是不太舒服
Yeah, well, I don't feel great, Felicity.

129
00:07:36,501 --> 00:07:39,401
要怎么才能好点呢?
Is there a right way to take that?

130
00:07:39,401 --> 00:07:40,867
你应该回去休息
You should go home.

131
00:07:40,867 --> 00:07:42,867
就要回去了
I am going.

132
00:07:42,867 --> 00:07:45,467
我要安排一个替班保镖
I just need to make arrangements for a replacement bodyguard.

133
00:07:45,467 --> 00:07:48,334
你接种过防流感疫苗吗? 我是没有
Did you get the flu shot? Personally, I never do.

134
00:07:48,334 --> 00:07:51,434
虽然知道有必要接种 但是我晕针
I know that I should. I just, I have this thing about needles.

135
00:07:51,434 --> 00:07:53,234
所有尖的东西 我都害怕
All pointy things, really.

136
00:07:53,234 --> 00:07:55,334
讽刺的是 我们还得跟用弓箭的人搭伙工作
Which is ironic, considering who we work with.

137
00:07:55,334 --> 00:07:57,568
这不是流感 Felicity 感觉更像是...
Yeah, it's not the flu, Felicity, it's more like...

138
00:07:57,568 --> 00:08:00,034
Dig! 你怎么了?
Dig!

139
00:08:00,034 --> 00:08:03,201
有人吗?
Hello?

140
00:08:03,201 --> 00:08:05,534
你在吗?
Are you here?

141
00:08:05,534 --> 00:08:08,467
在这里... 在那里...
Here... there...

142
00:08:08,467 --> 00:08:10,568
无处不在
Everywhere.

143
00:08:10,568 --> 00:08:12,301
那么
So.

144
00:08:12,301 --> 00:08:14,634
我们的科研进展如何?
How goes our little science project?

145
00:08:14,634 --> 00:08:16,833
跟你预期的一样
Working like you said it would.

146
00:08:16,833 --> 00:08:18,800
真不错
How wonderful.

147
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,668
听我说
Ah, so listen.

148
00:08:20,668 --> 00:08:23,800
研究的薪酬是五万块
Doing the thing was 50,000.

149
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,800
要想让我封口的话
Keeping quiet about it,

150
00:08:25,800 --> 00:08:28,000
就得给我二十五万
I'm thinking it should be 50 more.

151
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,401
是吗
Hmm.

152
00:08:29,401 --> 00:08:31,568
我不需要封口
Oh, I want word to spread.

153
00:08:31,568 --> 00:08:34,800
实际上 这是我计划的一部分
It's kind of the whole objective, actually.

154
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:37,701
懂我的意思吗?
You see my point?

155
00:08:40,034 --> 00:08:43,567
你应该知道 事后谈判...
You should know, I find post hoc negotiation...

156
00:08:43,567 --> 00:08:45,800
收场不会愉快的
Distasteful.

157
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:47,601
啊
Ahh.

158
00:08:47,601 --> 00:08:49,434
真遗憾 医生
Such a shame you won't get to see

159
00:08:49,434 --> 00:08:51,833
你看不到自己的杰作了
what your works have wrought, doctor.

160
00:08:51,833 --> 00:08:55,367
但是过不了多久 大家都会感受到的
But soon, everyone else will.

161
00:08:55,715 --> 00:09:00,121
而他们会求我结束痛苦
And they'll beg for me to end.

162
00:09:09,301 --> 00:09:11,106
你怎么会在这里?
What the hell are you doing here?

163
00:09:11,107 --> 00:09:12,366
我听说你晕倒了?
I heard you passed out.

164
00:09:12,441 --> 00:09:14,041
我告诉Felicity不要给你打电话
I told Felicity not to call you.

165
00:09:14,041 --> 00:09:15,541
没错 在此之前 你还说了"水沟" 和"子弹"
Yeah, but before that, you said "gaw" and "thud,"

166
00:09:15,541 --> 00:09:17,241
不过我没太在意
So I didn't take it very seriously.

167
00:09:17,241 --> 00:09:19,408
他给我电话是明智之举 Diggle 你需要去医院 
She was right to call me. Diggle, you need medical attention.

168
00:09:19,408 --> 00:09:21,220
他需要的不止是去医院 Dig昏厥的时候
He needs more than that. When Dig passed out,

169
00:09:21,227 --> 00:09:23,374
我采集了他的血液样本 送到一位搞质量检测的化学师那里检测
I sent a sample of his blood to a chemist I know at QC.

170
00:09:23,381 --> 00:09:25,714
那家伙欠我一个人情 一言难尽 我帮他搞定了违章罚单
The guy owes me a favor. Long story, I fixed his parking ticket.

171
00:09:25,714 --> 00:09:27,747
啊哈 也不是一言难尽
Huh. I guess it's not that long.

172
00:09:27,747 --> 00:09:30,614
Felicity 重点是血液样本检测
Felicity. The blood sample.

173
00:09:30,614 --> 00:09:33,614
没错 检测结果显示... 迷魂药检阳性
Yeah. It came back positive... for trace amounts of vertigo.

174
00:09:33,614 --> 00:09:34,747
我从来没服用过迷魂药
I never used vertigo before in my life.

175
00:09:34,747 --> 00:09:36,547
可能是无意间摄入的
You were exposed to it somehow.

176
00:09:36,547 --> 00:09:38,014
迷魂药又出现了?
Vertigo's in play again?

177
00:09:38,014 --> 00:09:39,714
"伯爵"从他的迷魂药恢复过来后
